quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  21,94,"So whoever does deeds of righteousness, and he is a believer, then there will be no disavowal of his endeavor; and surely We write it down for him"
  21,95,"And it is prohibited for any town We have caused to perish that they will not return. (Literally: that they do not return to this world)"
  21,96,"Till, when Yajuj and Majuj (Gog and Magog) are opened up, and they press down from every slope, (i.e., broken themselves into sects)"
  21,97,"And the True Promise has drawn near; so, only then, do the beholdings of the ones who disbelieved (keep) glazing (i.e., eyesights) over. \"O woe to us! We were already in (a state of) heedlessness of this; no indeed, we were unjust"
  21,98,Surely you and whatever you worshiped apart from Allah are gravel for Hell; you will herd (yourselves) down to it
  21,99,"If these had been gods, in no way would they have herded themselves down to it; and all of them are therein eternally (abiding)"
  21,100,"Therein there will be groaning for them, and therein they will not hear (anything)"
  21,101,"Surely the ones to whom the fairest reward has gone before from Us, those will be kept far from it"
  21,102,"They will not hear its perceptible (hissing) sound, and they are eternally (abiding) in whatever their selves craved for. (Literally: lusted for)"
  21,103,"The greatest alarm will not grieve them, and the Angels will receive them: \"This is your Day that you were promised"
  21,104,"The Day when We will fold the heaven as the Recorder's folding of the Books. As We began the first creation, We will bring it back again -a promise (binding) on Us. Surely We have been Performers"
  21,105,"And indeed We have already written in the Scripture, (The Zabur = the Psalms) even after the Remembrance, (that) \"My righteous bondmen will inherit the earth"
  21,106,Surely in this is indeed a proclamation to a worshiping people
  21,107,And in no way have We sent you except as a mercy to the worlds
  21,108,"Say, \"Surely what is revealed to me is only that your God is (only) one God; so will you then be Muslims?\" (i.e., those who surrender (to Allah)"
  21,109,"So if they turn away, then say, \"I have notified you (all) equally, and decidedly I do not realize whether what you are promised is near or far"
  21,110,"Surely He knows what is spoken aloud, (literally: loud saying) and He knows what you keep back"
  21,111,"And decidedly I do not realize (that) perhaps it would be a temptation for you, and an enjoyment for a while.\" (i.e., your disbelief)"
  21,112,"He said, \"Lord! Judge with the truth! And our Lord is The All-Merciful; His help is to be sought against whatever you describe"